2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed scheme is intended for use in wireless communication systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper considers the multi-user scenario, which involves the study of social and information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed scheme aims to improve the sum rate of the system, which is a performance metric relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes techniques such as trellis coding and scaling, which are commonly used in machine learning.
